#Text=The Milwaukee Bucks ( 18 - 17 ) defeated the New York Knicks ( 5 - 31 ) 95 - 82 on Sunday at Madison Square Garden in New York .
#Text=The Bucks were able to have a great night defensively , giving themselves the scoring advantage in all four quarters .
#Text=The Bucks showed superior shooting , going 46 percent from the field , while the Knicks went only 41 percent from the floor .
#Text=The Bucks also out - rebounded the Knicks 48 - 36 , giving them in an even further advantage which helped them secure the 13 - point victory on the road .
#Text=Brandon Knight led the Bucks again in this one .
#Text=He went 6 - for - 14 from the field and 1 - for - 3 from beyond the arc to score 17 points , while also handing out five assists .
#Text=He 's now averaging 21 points per game over his last three games , as he 's consistently been the offensive leader for this team .
#Text=Zaza Pachulia also had a strong showing , finishing with 16 points ( 6 - 12 FG , 4 - 4 FT ) and a team - high of 14 rebounds .
#Text=It marked his second double - double in a row and fourth on the season , as the inexperienced centers on the Knicks ' roster were n't able to limit him .
#Text=Notching a double - double of his own , Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded 16 points ( 6 - 9 FG , 1 - 1 3Pt , 3 - 6 FT ) and 12 rebounds .
#Text=The 12 rebounds matched a season - high , while it was his second double - double of the season .
#Text=Coming off the bench for a big night was Kendall Marshall .
#Text=He went 6 - for - 8 from the field and 3 - for - 3 from the free throw line to score 15 points in 20 minutes .
#Text=The Knicks really struggled to score without Carmelo Anthony and Amare Stoudemire .
#Text=Tim Hardaway Jr led the team as the starting shooting guard , going 6 - for - 13 from the field and 3 - for - 5 from the three - point line to score 17 points , while also adding four assists .
#Text=He 's now scored 17 or more points in three out of his last four games , as he has put it on himself to pick up the slack with other key players sitting out .
#Text=J.R.
#Text=Smith also put together a solid outing as a starter .
#Text=He finished with 15 points and seven rebounds in 37 minutes .
#Text=Like Haradaway Jr , he 's also benefitted from other guys sitting out , and has now combined for 37 points over his last two games .
#Text=While he did n't have his best night defensively , Cole Aldrich scored 12 points ( 6 - 10 FG ) and grabbed seven rebounds in 19 minutes .
#Text=The only other Knick to reach double figures in points was Jason Smith , who came off the bench for 10 points ( 3 - 11 FG , 4 - 4 FT ) .
#Text=The Bucks ' next game will be at home against the Phoenix Suns on Tuesday , while the Knicks will travel to Memphis to play the Grizzlies on Monday .
